ly: \'Times New Roman\'; color: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Fortnite</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">&nbsp;and the game\'s various updates</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">&nbsp;and content overhauls, announcing even the smallest weapon and balance changes on its numerous social media channels.</span></p>', 'Admin', '2025-02-06 12:16:38', 'uploads/67a4a826311d7.jpg', 1, 4, NULL, 0),
(33, 'Call of Duty: Black Ops 6 Players Can Claim 2 Free Operator Skins, But There\'s a Catch', '<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Call of Duty: Black Ops 6&nbsp;</span></strong></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">players can now claim a free Season 2 bundle that includes 2 operator skins, 3 weapon blueprints, double XP tokens, and much more. Unfortunately, there is a catch, as this Season 2 bundle can only be claimed by&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/db/video-game/call-of-duty-black-ops-6/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Call of Duty: Black Ops 6</span></em></a></span><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">or&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">Warzone&nbsp;</span></em>players on PlayStation 4 or PlayStation 5 who are also subscribed to the platform\'s popular subscription service, PS Plus.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Fans have been left somewhat baffled by the new PS Plus bundle, as&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">Call of Duty</span></em>\'s publisher, Activision, is now owned by Sony\'s competitor, Microsoft. In October 2023,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/microsoft-acquires-activision-blizzard/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Microsoft officially completed its acquisition of Activision-Blizzard,</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;which cost a massive $68.7 billion and was the biggest acquisition in video game history. Now that Activision is under the Microsoft umbrella, many of the studio\'s titles have begun making their way to Xbox Game Pass, including the recently released&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">Call of Duty: Black Ops 6</span></em>. However, despite the acquisition now being over a year old, it looks like PS Plus users are still getting some extra&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">Call of Duty&nbsp;</span></em>benefits that Xbox users aren\'t.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">How To Get Free Black Ops 6 Season 2 Bundle With PS Plus</span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">On February 4, a new bundle for&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 18.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/call-of-duty-black-ops-6-season-2-update-patch-notes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; color: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Call of Duty: Black Ops 6&nbsp;</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Season 2</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">&nbsp;made its way to the PlayStation Store. Unlike many other&nbsp;</span><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">Call of Duty&nbsp;</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">bundles, this one can be claimed for free, but only by users who are currently subscribed to PlayStation Plus. The bundle includes 2 operator skins, 3 weapon blueprints, 2 animated emotes, a weapon charm, a weapon reticle, an emblem, a background, 2 stickers, 2 double XP tokens (1 hour), and 2 double weapon XP tokens (1 hour). To claim the bundle, subscribe to PlayStation Plus and&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 18.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Calibri\',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\"><a href=\"https://store.playstation.com/en-us/product/UP0002-CUSA23827_00-CODBO6PLUSPACK01\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">visit the store page for the bundle</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">&nbsp;to redeem it. The contents of the bundle will then be added to the user\'s&nbsp;</span><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">Call of Duty&nbsp;</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: KHM;\">account, but it is worth noting that the terms and conditions of the bundle state that the pack is not cross-platform supported.</span></p>', 'Admin', '2025-02-06 12:17:39', 'uploads/67a4a86309b61.jpg', 1, 4, NULL, 0),
(34, 'Dead by Daylight Releases New Update for February 2025', '<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Dead by Daylight</span></em></strong><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">\'s February 2025 update has been released. With the eight-year-old competitive horror game showing no signs of slowing down,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/db/video-game/dead-by-daylight/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Dead by Daylight</span></em></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;puts out these regular patches to keep gameplay competitive. Especially with the amount of new Killers and perks that have been added, many old mechanics are in need of some major tweaking.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">One of the most requested changes involves The Nightmare\'s play style. Many fans believe that Freddy Krueger\'s power set was in need of a massive overhaul, especially with the diverse roster that the Killer section possesses. A&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/dead-by-daylight-the-nightmare-upcoming-changes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">January 2025&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">Dead by Daylight</span></em>&nbsp;Developer Update</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;detailed some of the new things planned for The Nightmare. And while the patch that previously went live completely renewed the character, other issues arose from it which needed further correction.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">The February 2025 Dead by Daylight tweaks some factors relating to&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/dead-by-daylight-best-builds-nightmare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; background: white; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Dead by Daylight</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; background: white; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">\'s The Nightmare</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">&nbsp;and fixes other bugs and issues. New FX has been added when The Nightmare teleports to a healing Survivor. His Black Box add-on was also updated to block exit gates for sleeping survivors for 15 seconds after being opened. These small changes help define Freddy Krueger\'s playstyle even more. However, many other bugs involving other items and characters were also adjusted to allow for smoother gameplay.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">What\'s Been Updated in Dead by Daylight Version 8.5.1?</span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Perhaps the biggest addition to the February 2025 patch is the preparation of the return of&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/dead-by-daylight-2v8-mode-what-fog-project-t-casting-frank-stone/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Dead by Daylight</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">\'s 2v8 mode</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">. While older iterations of the mode featured a small selection of playable Killers, this new version is a two-week event that will feature a tome that offers&nbsp;</span><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-theme-font: major-fareast; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Resident Evil</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">-themed rewards. The said mode will be playable on February 10 and will also add The Legion, The Nemesis, and The Mastermind to the selectable characters on the Killer side. New maps such as the Raccoon City Police Department will also be available for play in 2v8.</span></p>', 'Admin', '2025-02-06 12:18:09', 'uploads/67a4a881c53a6.jpg', 1, 4, NULL, 0),
(35, 'Pokemon TCG Pocket Leak Teases Upcoming Event', '<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">A new&nbsp;<em><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">Pokemon TCG Pocket</span></strong></em>&nbsp;leak has revealed an upcoming distribution event that will give rare cards to players. Like physical cards,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://gamerant.com/db/video-game/pokemon-trading-card-game-pocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Pokemon TCG Pocket</span></em></a>&nbsp;players can get a selection of rare cards to add to their collections. To do this, they open booster packs, counting themselves lucky to pull these coveted cards or gather enough pack points to craft them.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-ptcgp-card-raritiy-rates-diamond-star-crown-explained/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Pokemon TCG Pocket</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">&nbsp;cards are divided by rarity</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">, the lowest being one-diamond and the highest being the crown cards. While diamond cards have a 100% chance of appearing from the first to the third slot of a booster pack, crown cards only have a 0.040% chance of dropping in the fourth slot and a 0.16% chance of appearing in the fifth slot. Obtaining the rarest cards in the game requires a good dose of luck and patience, but a new leak brings promising news for players.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">According to a&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.pokemon-zone.com/events/genetic-apex-presents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; background: white; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">leak shared by Pokemon Zone</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">,&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Pokemon TCG Pocket</span></em>&nbsp;will have a distribution event giving away cards of rarity four-diamond upwards. The information says that the event will start on February 27, and three packs from the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-all-cards-best-worst-genetic-apex/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; background: white; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">Genetic Apex expansion</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">&nbsp;will be given away; one of Pikachu, Charizard, and Mewtwo. While this will be a great chance for players to pull coveted cards, there is a twist: only the fifth card in each pack will be rare, with the others being regular. The leak also informs that players will have until April 30 to claim the packs in their Gift Box.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Pokemon TCG Pocket Leaked Genetic Apex Expansion Distribution Event Details</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Event date: February 27 to April 30</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Rewards: a Pikachu, Charizard, and Mewtwo booster pack (guaranteed rare card in the fifth slot)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">The four-diamond rarity cards in the Genetic Apex set are the regular ex, which includes popular names like Mewtwo, Blastoise, and Exeggutor. The one-star rarity are the full art rare cards, the two-star rarity are the full art ex and trainer cards, and the three-star rarity are the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-how-get-all-immersive-cards/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">immersive&nbsp;<em>Pokemon TCG Pocket</em>&nbsp;cards</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">. The crown rarity cards are the most difficult to see in the game and are the ex with golden backgrounds featuring Pikachu, Charizard, and Mewtwo.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">As with other leaks, players should take this information with a grain of salt as there has been no official confirmation from the developers. In the meantime, other events are officially available. One of them is giving players&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-solo-battles-cresselia-ex-drop-event-new-promo-cards/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">new&nbsp;<em>Pokemon TCG Pocket</em>&nbsp;promo cards</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">, including Cresselia ex. Like the Lapras event, this is the only way to get the ex variant of the Gen 4 Legendary. The other is the PvP event, which is giving away themed badges from the new Space-Time Smackdown expansion.</span></p>', 'Admin', '2025-02-06 12:18:44', 'uploads/67a4a8a4d9eb9.jpg', 1, 4, NULL, 0),
(36, 'FC 25 Releases Title Update 9', '<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></strong></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;has recently released its Title Update 9 for all platforms. While the new update is not as large as some previous ones, it&rsquo;s still good to see Electronic Arts continuing to support&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/db/video-game/ea-sports-fc-25/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;by squashing bugs and improving the overall experience.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">&nbsp;is the latest entry in EA&rsquo;s famous soccer franchise and was released in September 2024. Over the months, EA has released several&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/ea-sports-fc-25-title-update-7-patch-notes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm;\">updates for&nbsp;</span><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">, ranging from minor tweaks to some major changes, each time improving the game&rsquo;s quality and stability.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">Now,&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: DaunPenh; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em>&rsquo;s new Title Update 9 has been released for all platforms. Most gamers should not expect any drastic changes in the new update, however, as it mainly fixes some glitches and makes some improvements to the game. For example, the update introduced the ability to search for OVR ranges in Club, SBCs, Rush, and Evolutions in the Ultimate Team mode, and added the ability to set Board Strictness in Live Starting Points in Career Mode.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"adsninja-injected-repeatable-ad-beforebegin\" style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Overall, Update 9 is much smaller than&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/ea-sports-fc-25-gameplay-refresh-update-patch-notes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm;\">&rsquo;s mid-season update</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">, which was one of the most significant patches the popular soccer game has received so far. For instance, the update changed how attacking and defense work in&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em>&nbsp;to make the experience feel more realistic. Also, EA has improved the quality of the teammate&rsquo;s AI while attacking to support player feedback better.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Despite EA&rsquo;s efforts to keep polishing&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">EA Sports FC 25</span></em>, it&rsquo;s fair to say that the game did not fare as well as intended. In a recent report, EA concluded that&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/dragon-age-the-veilguard-sales-underperformed-ea-expectations/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\">EA Sports FC 25&nbsp;</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm;\">performed below expectations</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">, not being able to sell as many copies as expected by the publisher.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 150%; background: white; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Not everything is looking grim for the&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">EA Sports FC&nbsp;</span></em>series, however. Recent reports indicate that&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://gamerant.com/ea-tech-company-acquisition-fc-series-realism/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0cm; padding: 0cm;\">Electronic Arts has recently acquired TRACAB Technologies</span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">, a company that specializes in collecting data from real-world soccer games. With the technology provided by TRACAB, it&rsquo;s possible that future&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">EA Sports FC&nbsp;</span></em>games will have even more realistic gameplay, as the developers will have additional data about how to emulate the real-life movement of players. In any case, it&rsquo;s still unclear whether this tech will be applied to the upcoming&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">EA Sports FC 26</span></em>, which is expected to be released late in 2025, and it&rsquo;s possible that it will only affect later titles.</span></p>', 'Admin', '2025-02-06 12:19:19', 'uploads/67a4a8c7755c6.jpg', 1, 4, NULL, 0);
